[[Goblin|goblin]]s and [[kobold]]s have long been oppressed in the barrens of [[Droaam]], being dismissed as small and weak by the [[ogre]]s, [[troll]]s, and their kin. But there have always been those whose fury and determination to bring down their enemies—no matter their size—has drawn the favor of the [[Devourer]] and unlocked the predator within them. Known as the //gaa’taarka//, or wolfchildren, these champions develop the gift of [[wild shape]]. While they are most often associated with wolf form, they aren’t limited to it; there are gaa’taarka who can scout as hawks or fight as bears. Wolfchildren have often served as champions defending their kin from would-be oppressors. Today, a number of gaa’taarka have joined the [[Great Pack]], while others are serving with [[Maenya's Fist]]. 